      <h1 class="cw-h1">Index Theologicus</h1>
      <p>The Index Theologicus (IxTheo) is an international open access bibliography for theology and religious studies. It provides information on scholarly literature about Christianity as well as about the dialog with other religions. The bibliography references historical and current publications in multiple languages and formats concerning all confessions and denominations.</p>
      <p>Its editors are the <a target="_blank" href="https://uni-tuebingen.de/en/facilities/university-library/">Universitätsbibliothek Tübingen (University Library of Tübingen</a>, the <a target="_blank" href="https://uni-tuebingen.de/en/fakultaeten/evangelisch-theologische-fakultaet/fakultaet/aktuelles/">Evangelisch-Theologische Fakultät Tübingen (the Protestant faculty of theology of the university of Tübingen)</a> and the <a target="_blank" href="https://uni-tuebingen.de/en/faculties/faculty-of-catholic-theology/faculty/">Katholisch-Theologische Fakultät Tübingen (the Catholic faculty of theology of the university of Tübingen)</a>.</p>
      <p>The specialized bibliographies <a target="_blank" href="https://bible.ixtheo.de/">Index Biblicus</a> und <a target="_blank" href="https://churchlaw.ixtheo.de/?lng=en">Index Canonicus</a> are produced and published in cooperation with the following partners: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.uibk.ac.at/bildi/index.html.en">BILDI (Innsbruck)</a> and <a target="_blank" href="https://www.unil.ch/ftsr/en/home/menuinst/recherche/instituts/irsb.html">BiBIL (Lausanne)</a> for the Index Biblicus, <a target="_blank" href="https://www.uni-muenster.de/FB2/ikr/datenbank/index.shtml">DaKaR (Münster)</a> and <a target="_blank" href="https://www.uibk.ac.at/en/praktheol/kirchenrecht/kaldi/">KALDI (Innsbruck)</a> for the Index Canonicus.</p>
      
