      <h3><b>Contents</b></h3>
      <p>The Index Theologicus provides references to monographs, essay collections, journals, journal articles, lexicon articles, reviews, databases, archival documents, personal archives, blogs, podcasts, research data and other contents which are electronically available from all fields of theology. We catalogue literature in many languages and formats concerning all confessions and denominations.</p>
      <p>Our database includes current theological literature in many languages and historical titles going as far back as the 16th century.</p>
      <p>We catalogue the contents of over 1200 international journals in theology and religious studies on a regular basis, referencing all articles and reviews. Many journals have been catalogued completely up to their very first issue. We are also continuing to catalogue essays from older collections.</p>
      <p>Our database currently holds approximately 4.5 million entries.</p>
      <p>More detailed information is available under  <a href="/#ixtheo-content">IxTheo Content</a>.</p>

